The paper discusses the safety of machine learning algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the foundational principle of modern statistical machine learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses strategies for achieving safety in engineering, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the harm incurred by unwanted outcomes, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses safety in cyber-physical systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
